laboratory_examinations.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis noted. Enlarged right atrium. Liver demonstrates homogeneous attenuation, no focal lesions or biliary dilatation, cholelithiasis without cholecystitis. Normal pancreas and spleen. Bilateral renal hypodensities suggestive of cysts, right-sided extrarenal pelvis. Inflamed diverticulum of sigmoid colon with surrounding soft tissue stranding and wall thickening. Trace amount of free fluid in pelvis. No abdominopelvic lymphadenopathy. Moderate to severe atherosclerotic disease noted.
MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
